rComments: Just save yourself the headache and take this course with someone else. His lectures are him writing on a chalkboard which you can barely see. Homework at the end of each class of the material we just learned. final exam? horrible. He didn't give us any prep or info prior to the exam. My GPA may suffer because of his lack of teaching abilities :(

HSS3510- 3-hour class of not understanding what we were talking about. Doesn't know how to communicate the course content. If taken online, you can't read anything written on chalkboard. Take with another prof if possible. Labs and course content do not reflect whats on the exams. The midterms are 3 hours long, stuff is due after each class. AVOID
I hated this professor and this class. He was arrogant, rude and laughed at students' questions... His exams were difficult and did not reflect the material viewed in class.
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Lots of homework', 'Beware of pop quizzes']

rComments: Reading the textbook is necessary, as well as practice exercises! Bases all the exam questions off the textbook, if you do the practice the tests will be easy. Very helpful with questions during office hours and over email. My only critique is that the textbook is in English for a french class, and that his explanations aren't always clear.

AVOID AT ALL COST !! He doesn't know what he is talking about that. "Jeu-questionnaire" at the beginning of every classes about the material of the day !? Exercises at the end of every class too. French class - the textbook is in English !? Exam way too long, and based on the English textbook. I am doing okay but some of us don't speak English !

This teacher does NOT care about his students success, he even mocks you when asking questions. The textbook is only offered in english when the class is strictly in french, which is unfair for non-billigual students. His classes consist of him solving problems that the students dont even have access to the question at hand. Also very rude.

Le premier cours de stat que j'ai jamais pris et la pire expérience que j'aurais pu avoir. Le prof n'est PAS clair du tout dans ses explications ni dans ses attentes des étudiants. Il nous explique très brièvement des concepts de statisque complexes, qui sont unique à son cours à lui. Si vous pouvez prendre ce cours avec quelqu'un d'autre faite le.

rComments: If you care about your GPA and actually learning, avoid this prof at all costs. The mandatory manual for this class (a FRENCH class might I add) is in english, and some of his notes are in english and he refuses to translate them. I'm lucky I'm bilingual, but not everyone is and it's unfair to them to only have access to a textbook in english.
The worst

This is the worst prof I've ever had. The midterms do not reflect the material seen in class. He gave us a 3 hour long MIDTERM. He almost makes fun of those who don't understand. The class average for the first midterm was 40%. No powerpoint all on chalkboards. He doesn't even have a science degree & clearly has no idea what he's doing. AVOID!!

His teaching is all over the place and his explanations arent clear. He gave us his email but told us not to email him any questions as he doesnt want to answer. His question formulation is very unclear. He says if most of the class fails, it doesnt reflect his teaching. Asked a question once, his reply was its simple and he walked away.

Terrible teacher that doesn't even make sense when explaining pretty basic stuff. He even says himself that he teaches stuff a introduction class shouldn't even see. Class in itself isn't that hard but the teacher is the worst at explaining and the exams have nothing to do with the things seen in class.
Has a difficult time explaining material. Goes through material very quickly. Exams are not reflective of examples.
very frustrating class, hard to do good because the exercises are nothing like the exam, avoid him if you can

Special I would say. He's a nice, really intelligent guy (even too intelligent to be a professor). He thinks he makes sense but he doesn't. The material on the exam come out of nowhere and he doesn't give enough practice. I would avoid this prof.

Prof goes very fast during class when explaining new material. He replies very quickly to questions in class. Midterms were very hard and not similar to what was given as exercises during the class. He does not use any slides or notes. He just reads out loud and uses the chalk board. His "bonus questions" on his exams do not give you extra points.

Excellent teacher. Knows what he's talking about, but sometimes has trouble putting into words so students understand. Dont be afraid to ask questions. Make sure you UNDERSTAND, dont try to learn by heart. Midterms are relatively easy, finals are tough.

J'ai eu ce prof 3 X  en Stats, Développement Épidémio. Super ! il est super gentil, toujours là pour répondre aux question, n'ayez pas peur de lui poser des question et même lui faire répéter 3-4X si nécessaire, il va tout essayer pour vous faire comprendre! Développement était beaucoup plus complexe, il faut travailler pour mériter les notes.

j'ai eu cet enseignant 3 fois en 3 ans. ce professeur est un bon chercheur mais un très mauvais enseignant. il ne connait pas la matière qu'il doit enseigner, et est lui-même confus dans ses propres notes. il fait plusieurs erreurs en enseignant et n'ajuste pas les évaluations de façon juste. Si possible, il est préférable d'éviter ces cours.
HE DOESNT KNOW HOW WELL THE MATEIAL THAT HIS TEACHING. MOST OF PPL WHO TAKE THIS COURSE WITH HIM FAIL. U GOT TO TAKE IT TO TIME OR DROP IT.
This prof is quite the caracter!!!! He has no clue himself what he wants. Directives are so vague. Went to see him many times and makes you feel like you should be able to read his mind.

Les laboratoires sont très compliquer et je n'est pour la pluspart rien compris de ce qu'il fallait vraiment faire... De plus, son livre de base est en anglais donc pour ceux que ce n'est pas la langue première, ce n'est pas conseiller. Examen très long, vous avez à y répondre vite. Il a souvent l'air perdu dans ces propres notes de cours..
One of the best profs I've ever had!
One of the best profs I've ever had!      H-O

Les mi-sessions étaient relativement faciles, basés énormément sur le livre. Donc, lire le livre! Par contre, l'exam final est plus difficile, plusieurs questions revenaient plusieurs fois,donc il faut s'assurer de COMPRENDRE tous les concepts et apprendre la théorie pour bien réussir. Le prof est sympathique et veut que ces étudiants réussissent.

J'aime bien ce prof et sa manière d'enseigner, quoi qu'il est vrai qu'il faut bien écouter pour savoir que prendre en notre au bon moment de ce qu'il écrit au tableau, mais si on lit le livre et ses notes avant le cours c'est très bien.

His notes are all over the place as others have said. His midterm exams were fine, although many questions were worded weirdly. His final exam however was just bad. He introduced several new concepts that I had never seen before and had to guess and figure out on my own during the exam. I managed to do ok though a third of the class failed(Avg. 59)

Nice guy, but very confusing when teaching. hes all over the place...also the small works worth 15% are impossible to do well on. No grading chart to know what he expects...just bad grades. everyone complains but he just says thats how it is. Also his exams are veryyyy long!

He is not my favorite prof but I wouldn't push him in front of a bus either. He is very nice and understanding. Make sure to study your book really well. He likes to give alot of exam questions. The work he gives is difficult. The work he gives will increase your grade.

Horrible professeur! This teacher is all over the map! He is incomprehensible and his teaching methods are only for people who already understand what he is talking about. Sympathique, mais méfiez vous de l'examen, très long, moins de 1 minute par problème (mise en situation avec calculs à faire)
Mauvais professeur! Aime compliquer la matière pour rien et adore donner plus de devoirs que nécessaire. Enseigne statistiques aussi et n?étais pas meilleur dans ce cours.
